<br>
The problem is, with our server coding messed up as badly as it is, the only real solution is to implement no drop in the same form that it is on other servers. I won a +6 wisdom aug with Kolani in a LDoN group the other night, and promptly installed it on Kolyene's Coldain Skin gloves by logging Koly in, trading the gloves, installing the augument and handing them back to Koly. Not a key to a high level zone, but essentially the same thing that's happening with the keys.<br>
<br>
If we apply this to the Sleeper’s/Vex Thal keys, we need to apply it to all no drop items. There’s a topic somewhere here about someone wanting to buy adventure points. That augument is no drop, the poster is basically asking for someone to purchase a no drop augument, install it on an item so that it becomes no drop and give it back to them. Which is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>EXACTLY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the same thing as putting a key in a bag, dropping it on the ground and picking it up.<br>
<br>
Even worse, all the parts that go into the making of these keys is droppable here. They're not on other servers, btw. Lucid Shards are no drop, Emp room key is no drop, Luclinite is no drop, planar rift is no drop, First Brood Talismans are no drop. If someone wants in those zones badly enough, they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>will</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> get in, and there is nothing Rollen, Absor or anyone can do about it. They'll camp the Bazaar, buy plat, buy the stuff off Boog, etc. Or go this route....<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Cleric is VP, ST, and VT keyed! <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
