<br>
Your examples aren't quite the same, Kolani.  Augmented items are not no drop on this server.  And, as far as I can tell, they weren't meant to be.  To me, the oversight is having all the augmentations be no drop.<br>
<br>
But the difference is the presence of the No Drop flag.  From what people are saying, I could sell my Staff of the Four to someone by putting it in a bag and dropping it so they could pick it up, despite the fact that it is no drop on this server.<br>
<br>
That is the problem people are talking about.  At least it was at the beginning.  Now, it seems to be turning into another &quot;uber vs non-uber&quot; argument, and I think we've had quite enough of those.<br>
<br>
To me, the solution is simple.  Make the keys droppable.  That's all that needs to be done.  Even with a VT key on your key ring, you have to survive long enough to reap the benefits of being in that zone. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/thewok/jarasig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
